article.headline: Colgate 21, Princeton 14, OT
article.story: PRINCETON, N.J. -- Nate Eachus had two 2-yard scoring runs in overtime and undefeated Colgate stopped Princeton on downs on the final possession for a 21-14 double-overtime victory Thursday night. Princeton tied it at 7 with 9:45 left in the fourth quarter on Tommy Wornham's 31-yard touchdown pass to Trey Peacock, and took a 14-7 lead in the first overtime on Wornham's 23-yard scoring pass to Andrew Kerr. Eachus then capped Colgate's next two possessions with his 2-yard scoring runs. Colgate quarterback Greg Sullivan had a 2-yard touchdown run in the second quarter. Colgate (6-0, 1-0 Patriot League) beat Princeton (1-3, 0-1 Ivy League) for the fifth time in the last six games in the series.
